<p>The <code>@variable:name</code> property returns a specific level-scoped variable value.</p>

<h2>Access Level Variables</h2>
<pre>{open}users myVar="test value"{close}
  {open}@first{close}
    Variable myVar: {open}@variable:myVar{close}
  {open}/@first{close}
{open}/users{close}</pre>

<p>Result:</p>
{users myVar="test value"}
  {@first}
    Variable myVar: {@variable:myVar}
  {/@first}
{/users}

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Level-scoped variables are set using the tag's named parameters. Use <code>@variable:varName</code> to access them. Returns NULL if not set.</p>
